deck: Heaven Sent Gaming is a publisher and entertainment production team from Albuquerque, New Mexico, USA, founded in 2006 by a married couple, Mario and Isabel Lucero. They have created multiple series spanning across multiple forms of media, including; comics, games, music, novels, video, and web entertainment.
description:
Origin

Isabel R. Lucero and Mario J. Lucero are high school sweethearts. While attending college together, from 2006-2007 they formed a game design team called Our Own Little Coup. That team consisted of several smaller groups, one of which was Mario and Isabel's Heaven Sent Gaming.

History

The Our Own Little Coup team members included Drew Cass, Devin Thurlow, and Jason Waggoner.

Mario and Isabel left college, in 2008, to take care of Mario's grandparents. It was during the later parts of 2008 that they began to work with independent music artists. And, in 2009, they completed their first comic strip of Reverie, which was published in 2010.

Timeline

2006

  • Founding of Our Own Little Coup and Heaven Sent Gaming

2007

  • First video released, 8-BIT HOMAGE - Age of Mythology

2008

  • Music album All We Are by Life Never Lost

2009

  • Introduction of video game news website, aywv
  • Music single Intro, Yo by Mario J. Lucero
  • Started accepting Bitcoin donations

2010

  • Introduction of Reverie

2011

  • Introduction of Karis
  • Introduction of Thad's World Destruction: Before Destruction
  • Introduction of video series HSGplays and Mario's vlog
  • Introduction of web novel series Many: The Blog of a Space Probe, Iron, and Craft

2012

  • Introduction of BladeChick
  • Introduction of Mouton

2013

  • Introduction of Koki'o Shade and Monkey

Published series

Comics

  • BladeChick
  • Karis
  • Koki'o Shade and Monkey
  • Mouton

  • Thad's World Destruction: Before Destruction

Novels

description:
Estrada Media Publishing was first formed by Jake Estrada. The first book to have been published by this imprint was Bocas. Bocas original run had 6 issues.

Bocas was a very violent no hold barred series that didn't pull it's punches. The series was originally printed in Black and White.

Many people either loved the series or were appalled by its violence. The Publisher had appeared in the paper a few times due to its graphic nature. Yet it touched about the urban landscape and was hugely entrenched in Puerto Rican politics.

Following Bocas there was the Prez Hates Zombies, Estrada Media Serials. Tainos. You cannot silence me, and many other titles.

During the 2007-2008 period Estrada Media Publishing dabbled in printing and they helped print several comics for many people throughout the Indie scene. They helped cultivate the next generation of creators during this very short period before ceasing this at the end of 2008.

Afterwards they resumed printing only their books, and they had a company rebranding as Bridgeton Nights, which was a very graphic shift for a period before that ended.

Afterwards the imprint moved under the Broken Infinite print for a while before merging with Space Coast Comixx in mid 2014. This merger taking all company owned characters with them.
name: Estrada Media Publishing
